						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged in places and incomplete. It is bilingual and records a gift of 20 gold coins to the temple of Tirukkīḻkōṭṭattu-Bhaṭṭāraka by <hi rend="bold">Kāchchuvaṉ</hi> (Kāśyapan) <hi rend="bold">Danapati Araṅgaṉ</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Pañchavaṉ•••• the headman of Karuvūr</hi> in Miḻalaikkūṟṟam. This may be assigned to <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I</hi> on account of the early writing and the high regnal year given for the king.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
